    <summary>A button box should be used to provide a consistent layout of buttons throughout your application. This box provides a way of laying out buttons horizontally.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>The specific layout of buttons in this type of box is determined by the box's <see cref="T:Gtk.ButtonBoxStyle" />.</para>
      <para>Methods for manipulating button boxes are provided in the super classes, <see cref="T:Gtk.ButtonBox" /> and <see cref="T:Gtk.Box" />.</para>
